==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Punctured
<hw>Punc"tured</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having
the surface covered with minute indentations or dots.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Produced by puncture; having the
characteristics of a puncture; <as>as, a <ex>punctured</ex>
wound</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pundit</ent>⟦br⟧
